The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks for concept learning, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of memory-augmented neural networks and reinforcement learning also suggests a focus on learning from limited data and improving performance over time, which are common themes in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the experiments involve image classification and outlier detection, which are common topics in the sub-categories of cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
